237 of the interior of any buildings or improvements on the
238 property upon the timely request of the owner pursuant to
239 subsection 11 of this section. Mere observation of the
240 property via a drive-by inspection or the like shall not be
241 considered sufficient to constitute a physical inspection as
242 required by this section.
243 13. A county or city collector may accept credit cards
244 as proper form of payment of outstanding property tax or
